"Adventure Time" is an American animated television series created by Pendleton Ward for Cartoon Network. The show originally began in 2008 with a pilot for "Random! Cartoons" on Nicktoons Network. The pilot quickly became a cult hit on YouTube when it was continually removed and then re-added by different sources. It launched as its own series on April 5, 2010, on Cartoon Network. Its fifth season began on November 12, 2012. The series is rated TV-PG for fantasy violence.
Series overview.
<onlyinclude></onlyinclude>
Each "Adventure Time" episode is about 11 minutes in length; pairs of episodes are often telecast in order to fill a half-hour program time slot. Seasons are 26 episodes long. The series has completed 4 seasons. Its fourth season ran from April 2, 2012, through October 22, 2012; the show's writers have begun work on the fifth season, which started airing on November 12, 2012. On January 28, 2013, it was officially announced that the show had been renewed for a sixth season.
Episodes.
Season 1 (2010).
Season 1 began on April 5, 2010 (with "Slumber Party Panic"), and ended on September 27, 2010 (with "Gut Grinder"). It contains 26 episodes.
Season 2 (2010–11).
Season 2 began on October 11, 2010 (with "It Came from the Nightosphere"), and ended on May 2, 2011 (with "Mortal Recoil (Part 2)"). It contains 26 episodes.
Season 3 (2011–12).
Season 3 began on July 11, 2011 (with "Conquest of Cuteness"), and ended on February 13, 2012 (with "Incendium (Part 1)"). It contains 26 episodes.
Season 4 (2012).
Season 4 began on April 2, 2012 (with "Hot to the Touch"), and ended on October 22, 2012 (with "The Lich (Part 1)"). It contains 26 episodes.
Season 5 (2012–13).
Season 5 began on November 12, 2012 (with "Finn the Human (Part 2)"), and will end with "Only Wizards Allowed" on an unannounced date. It will contain 26 episodes.
Season 6.
On January 28, 2013, it was officially announced that the show had been renewed for a sixth season.
